<h2 id="org2a2237a">Multiple Git Identities</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2a2237a">
<p>
Here is how to setup multiple git identities.
Set up multiple top level directories where your projects will live, then edit your git config. I need This to separate my personal projects from my employer or work related stuff.
</p>

<p>
Here is my example for My Personal Projects
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[includeIf <span style="font-style: italic;">"gitdir:~/Documents/Projects/"</span>]
    <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">path</span> = ~/Documents/Projects/.gitconfig
</pre>
</div>

<p>
And Here is an example for a work related one
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[includeIf <span style="font-style: italic;">"gitdir:~/Documents/work/Projects/"</span>]
    <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">path</span> = ~/Documents/work/Projects/.gitconfig
</pre>
</div>

<p>
And inside your .gitconfig you can set the relevent identities needed, it is a normal <a href="../programming/20230712200139-gitconfig.html#ID-dc00a2c6-6aa9-4c90-ba6d-6982067d2169">gitconfig</a>  so any setting can be applied here.
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[<span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">user</span>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">name</span> = <span style="font-style: italic;">"Real name"</span>
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">email</span> = <span style="font-style: italic;">"work.email@employer.com"</span>
</pre>
</div>
</div>
